description: Access violation by connected system with Ethernet
address not allowed by repeaterPortAccessTable and
repeaterPortAccessAction.
This variable identifies the port within the group
within the repeater for which this entry contains
management information. This value can never be
greater than rptrGroupPortCapacity for the
associated group.
variables.name: ITOUCH-REPEATER-MIB::repeaterPortIndex

description: This port has lost link integrity.
This variable identifies the port within the group
within the repeater for which this entry contains
management information. This value can never be
greater than rptrGroupPortCapacity for the
associated group.
variables.name: ITOUCH-REPEATER-MIB::repeaterPortIndex

description: This variable identifies the group containing the
port for which this entry contains infromation.
variables.name: ITOUCH-REPEATER-MIB::repeaterPortGroupIndex

description: This trap issued to indicate that a redundancy group has
experienced a path change. The offending group and
the new path are included in the trap.

event.Summary: Redundancy group changed its path to $v2

description: This variable identifies the group.
variables.name: ITOUCH-REPEATER-MIB::repeaterRedundancyGroupGroupIndex

description: This variable represents the index of the path which is
currently being used as the active path. This value may be
used as the value for repeaterRedundancyPathIndex to index the
path table.
variables.name: ITOUCH-REPEATER-MIB::repeaterRedundancyGroupOperPath
